title: President-elect of the United States
added: [[Joe Biden]] is the president-elect of the United States, having defeated incumbent [[Donald Trump]] in the [[2020 United States presidential election|2020 presidential election]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Live Blog / Joe Biden elected president: Live updates on the transition plan|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/live-blog/2020-11-11-biden-harris-transition-n1247340|date=November 11, 2020|publisher=NBC News}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Read former President George W. Bush's full statement congratulating President-elect Joe Biden |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/elections/2020/11/08/read-george-w-bushs-full-statement-congratulating-joe-biden/6214070002/ |accessdate=9 November 2020 |work=[[USA Today]] |date=8 November 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://edition.cnn.com/politics/live-news/trump-biden-election-results-11-07-20/index.html |title=Joe Biden elected president |work=CNN|date=7 November 2020 |accessdate=7 November 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/election-us-2020-54836636 |title=US Election 2020: Joe Biden wins the presidency |work=BBC News|date=7 November 2020 |accessdate=7 November 2020}}</ref>

title: President-elect of the United States
added: According to legal experts, use of the title "president-elect" is often informal, indicating the candidate projected to win in the electoral college vote. However, the candidate does not officially become the president-elect until "after the General Services Administration initiates the transfer of power by 'ascertaining' the election results and Congress officially counts the electoral votes on Jan. 6."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tampabay.com/news/florida-politics/elections/2020/11/16/what-do-we-mean-when-we-call-joe-biden-the-president-elect-politifact|title=What do we mean when we call Joe Biden the president-elect?|author=Kim, Noah Y.|publisher=Tampa Bay Times/Politifact|date=16 November 2020|accessdate=18 November 2020}}</ref>
